<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1749,2088]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
1. Shrubs or erect herb with stem up to ca. 
<quantity box="[599,658,1749,1770]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
long; internodes regularly spaced, nodes not rooting; petioles 1–5(9.5) cm long .... ...........................................................................................................................................................................................................2.
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,1749,2088]" pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="132">
- Stoloniferous herbs; stem up to ca. 
<quantity box="[558,630,1807,1828]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="132" unit="cm" value="100.0">100 cm</quantity>
long; internodes alternating between very short and long, nodes sometimes rooting; petioles (3) 
